The paper deals with graph algorithms and their sublinear versions, which are typically studied in the areas of data structures (cs.DS), discrete mathematics (cs.DM), computational complexity (cs.CC), computational geometry (cs.CG), and machine learning (cs.LG). The focus on graph properties and their testability also suggests that cs.DM and cs.CC are likely categories. The use of random order streams and the study of approximation algorithms may point towards cs.LG and cs.CG.
